messages.content: Nash presumably has initiative.

Erik unsheathes his sword and strikes Harriet twice.

It’s @Nash Edwardson!
Nash attacks Selle with his longsword.
((19 to hit))
((how much damage is that))
((it’s just a hit roll I’m waiting for atmey to prompt me to roll for damage but I can do that now if it hits))
((10 damage. If it hits.))
((I mean it’s Selle I figured Juni would answer))
(( So Selle takes 10 damage?))
((Yes))
Selle takes 10 damage and has to do a death saving throw, which she succeeds. She starts to vomit blood out of her mouth.

"Good job, Nash!" Orion hits Erik with an arrow.

"Locruz, take Yule and get out of here!" Erik calls out.

Locruz lifts up Selle and dashes out of the room. 

((That’s a success))

Ruth punches Erik as hard as she can.

Harriet dashes after Locruz and Selle.

Erik summons a magic wall separating Selle and Locruz from the people chasing them. 

It’s back to @Nash Edwardson!
“Shit.” Nash says. He tries to physically break through the wall by hitting it very hard.

The wall is immune to this, wasting Nash’s turn.

"Turn it off!" Orion misses his attack.

Locruz dashes again, getting out of the area. ((Split channel))
Locruz grabs a healing potion from the temple and gives it to Selle. "Drink it, you’ll stop slowing me down."

(( i assume you meant selle))
Selle drinks the healing potion.
"Ghrk... Looks more like you're the one rescuing *me* here..."
Selle's front is completely covered in blood.
((You have 1d4hp. Roll))
"Let’s get out of here now." He rushes out.
Selle runs after Locruz.
They arrive outside of the temple, though some priests have started to chase them now. Locruz rushes into the catacombs.
Selle follows in a rush.
((Roll acrobatics or athletics, your choice))
(9, acrobatics)
Priests manage to grab onto Selle in the catacombs and prevent further escape.
(( can i stab them ))
((Yes))
Selle pulls out a dagger and stabs the priests to get them off her.
((Roll))
(6 damage, 17 accuracy)

The priest falls back, bleeding heavily. 

Another priest attempts to heal the first one but gets suckerpunched by Locruz.

"Come on, let's go!"
Selle shouts at Locruz to keep running.
They go back to running. ((Roll acrobatics again))
They escape and end up back near Laura's base.

Selle stops to catch a breather and to wipe the blood off of her face.
"*cough* *cough* *cough*."
*Gah... What a close one... These clothes are completely ruined too.*
"What should we do now? *cough*"
"Uh, stranger danger alert." Laura approaches them with a dagger.

"*cough*, Relax, it's Yule"
Selle takes off her blonde wig and let's their natural white hair loose.
"Sheesh… What’s with the crossdressing then? Did you need to seduce someone?" She snickers.

*Crossdressing, huh... I guess my normal state is more masculine than I thought it was.*
"Just needed to be discrete. This was easier than the alternative... Anyway, do you have any spare clothes? I'm kind of not looking great right now."

"Wow, you’re really into this huh. Maybe you just wanna steal my vibe?" Laura.

"Can you guys be weird elsewhere. I’m here too." Locruz groans.

Selle shakes puts their hand on their face and shakes their head.
"I'm good at stealing people's vibes."
Selle looks at Locruz.
"You alright? You should tell me what happened while we were gone." Selle looks concerned for Locruz' wellbeing.
"Just got kept in that cell while they insisted I was working with the assassin who tried to kill the emperor." Locruz.

"What a bunch of insane people..."
Selle sighs deeply.
"I'm wondering if I'm gonna have to somehow figure out who *actually* stabbed the emperor. Because this bullshit of me being framed for it won't stop until I do so."

"Chances are the queen already knows." Locruz rolls his eyes. 

"It's worth considering. Any ideas on the culprit, Yule?" Laura.

Selle places their hand on their chin.
"It's tough. I'm a little weak on information since I spent a lot of time at the party trying to follow Asturian. One of the people I spoke to was Baron Aeolian Burr, but I doubt it's him, he's got his own thing going on. I saw Nash Edwardson at the party, too, and he seemed a bit lost?"
*Wait, lost? Didn't that really weird dream tell me that the place where Asturian was trying to go to **existed** a bit before he went there? That means someone from the party must have been there already? But how? Does that even mean what I think that means? Damnit...*
Selle shakes their head.
"Sorry, I was a bit lost in thought there. Actually, Locruz, he was guarding your cell, right? I mean Nash Edwardson. Did you speak with him at all? Outside of being poked about being an accomplice to murder, I mean."
*The Order has plenty to gain with the death of Aragon, considering Asturian tightens up the rules on magic and those most religious can cover up their usage as just God's gift to them... An inside job?*

"He's an obsessive little weirdo. He's the son of the Duchess, so he's got some weird stuff about that I guess. He seemed kind of insane. But too insane to do this, probably. Seems more like a useful idiot. The other 2 seemed normal enough for guards." Locruz. "Oh, right... And he was with Donald when the murder happened. He can't be responsible." 

"The baron was with Aliza Hamill. I saw that when I was at the party. You know who I didn't see though?" Laura.
"Hm? Who?" Selle tilts their head inquisitively.

"The general. He should've been on duty, right? But I basically haven't been able to find any info on his whereabouts around the time of the murder. And he's apparently been in fights with the emperor in the past. Emperor Aragon even tried to make him retire. I'm betting that's where the juicy drama is hiding." Laura.

"The general? I mean... I guess I wouldn't put it past him." Locruz.
"The general? Do we know where he is or what he's been doing as of late?"
"He should just be in the castle, right?" Locruz. "Regardless, I’m not getting involved. I’ll head back to the hellhounds now. See ya."

"Stay safe, alright?" To Locruz.
Selle sighs.
"Anywhere I can clean myself off here? It's disgusting being in clothes steeped in your own blood. Don't wanna change right in front of you either, sorry."
"Yeah, yeah… Go ahead."

Selle goes to the bathroom and dresses down, taking off the blood-stained clothes and putting on the usual outfit that they would wear as Yule. They re-apply the necessary bandages and take their medicine. After this, they come back to the room, looking a lot more refreshed.
Laura is passed out in bed at this point.

*Already sleepy, huh? It's only afternoon. I wanted to ask her more questions but it's a better idea to rest now considering how much damage I took.*
Selle lays down on the couch, and stares at the ceiling for a bit.
*I'm so tired. The wound is still healing so I guess it's impacted my ability to think. Can't even think...*
Selle is asleep.

Ruth punches Erik 3 times, only hitting once.

Harriet casts dispel magic on the wall, which is useless. "Take this barrier down or I shall kill you!"

"Heh. Sorry, but I’m not buying whatever you’re selling." He slashes at Ruth.

It’s Nash’s turn.
Nash makes an exasperated noise, then slashes at Erik.
((24 to hit))
It hits.
((4 for damage))

Orion misses another shot. 

Ruth hits him again.

Harriet casts Banishing Smite as a bonus action and hits him for 38 damage, sending him flying against the wall of the cell. "You cannot defeat us."

"Heh… Haha… Guess I might have to get serious after all…" Erik gets up casually and the insignia of cancer appears behind him, bathing everyone in dark light. The 2 halves of the symbol attach themselves to his arms, causing them to glow with terrifying power. He casually punches Ruth into unconsciousness.

It’s Nash’s turn.

“W… what the fuck?” Nash sweats. “What the hell!” 

He attempts to cast Searing Smite.
This is a bonus action, he still has a normal action.
Nash fucking HITS HIM with his SWORD.
((Roll))
((23 to hit))

It hits.

Orion misses his shot.

Harriet strikes him with another Banishing Smite.

Erik stabs Nash 3 times in a row for 19 damage. 

It’s Nash’s turn.
Taking 19 damage will kill Nash. His eyes roll into the back of his head.

Well, not kill. He's down though.

The battle between Harriet and Erik rages on, but the power difference is clear. Orion keeps his distance because Erik is staying at close ranged attacks. Eventually they're able to hurt him enough to break his concentration on the wall. An army of priests rush in, clearly annoying Erik. He vanishes without a trace the next second.

((End initiative so you're back up, just without health))
“Gghhh..” Nash makes a pained noise, stumbling backwards. Is.. he bleeding?
Yes, but it's not lethal.
“Great.” Nash says, voice raspy. “Won’t die this time.”

"What the hell was that guy!?" Orion sits down.

"…A servant of cancer." Harriet.
Nash blinks, attempting to collect himself. "I should have figured.. those degenerates." He winces. "Hey, does anyone want to patch me up a little?"
((450xp for that fight btw))
((finally level 2 woooo))
((also at level 2 I've unlocked this btw))
"You're done with this job, Nash. Head on home. We'll have to figure out how to fight against such a powerful force." Harriet.
Nash tries to stand. "Done..? I mean.. I can do more, for sure. Can't I?"

"There's nothing left to do here." Harriet.

"Plus... We should get back to the investigation tomorrow. We should get some more info in the morning." Orion.
"Right." Nash says placidly. "That makes sense. May I be excused, then?"
"You just were." Harriet.
Nash smiles at her. *Bitch.* He turns to Orion. "..Goodbye, then. I'll see you tomorrow."
"See you tomorrow." Orion.

Nash turns around mechanially and exits the building. His manor is close, so it's not a long walk back home. Even with his breathing stuttering and chest heaving from exertion, he still makes it to his house in no time, dripping hot blood all over the carpet.
Mother will have to clean that up.
"Is anyone home?" Nash calls out.
Mother answers the door. "Ah... Yes, Nash? Good evening."

"Good evening." He smiles at her, beatifically. "Can you do your fucking job and clean up after me anytime soon?" He gestures at the floor. "Look at that. The prodigal son has returned to you, leaking fluid. Ehe. Ehaha." He's not entirely sure what he's saying, but it sounds correct.
"Are you... Alright? Do you need to lay down?" She holds her hand out for him to take.

"I don't need to fucking lie down!" He snaps. "I need you to *do your job*, and I need to.. I need to do mine." He hisses. "I need to get this done... someone is endangering our goddess.. I need to *get this done.*"
"And... What job would that be? Do you want to go see Kori?"
Nash stares at her, confused. "What? Maybe. I don't know. I mean, can I.. can I keep her safe?" His head hurts. It's all throbbing. His heartbeat pulsing in his head.
"Is she in danger?"

Nash waves his hand dismissively. Why doesn't she understand this very simple concept? Is she stupid? "The whole *family* is under attack." He says, condescending. "All the time.. in so many different ways. Endless indignities. The sickness of the weak. Infidels. Perverts. Any that would corrupt, the uh, the fuckin'...." He trails off. Makes up his mind. "I wanna see Kori."
"Alright. She’s in her room."
Nash nods at her and exits. He walks up the stairs, still dripping blood everywhere, and raps on her door. Short and sharp, two knocks. As always. Their signal.
Kori opens the door. "What? Did you trip or something?"
Nash marches forwards in his haze and grabs her by the face, studying it for any sign of injury or distress. "Gweh.." He mutters, singlemindedly focused on this.
((Roll medicine))
You can’t be sure.
"Bah..." He mutters, dissatisfied. "Are you eating properly???" He demands.
"Yes…? What are you doing!?"
Nash draws back, cowed. "Urgh.. Can't I be concerned for you?" He laughs bitterly.
"You’re being a weirdo."
He scoffs. "*You're* weird." Nailed it.
"Ok."

He stares at her. Waiting for something. *Come on, thank me! I've showed investment in your circumstances, haven't I? Your health, haven't I? Don't you owe me something...? Some kind of kindness or acknowledgement or whatever? I don't give a fuck what it is! I know you have it!*
She sits down on her bed silently.

He stands in the doorway, swaying back and forth on his feet. Strands of hair fall in front of his eyes. Her small pale form is blurry. He becomes fixated on the movement of her legs, back and forth, trailing off the side of the bed in rhythmic pendulous movements. He's still waiting, dammit!
"What do you want?"
He blinks at her, sluggish. "I 'unno."
"What?"
"I dunno!"
He backs away.
"Fine. If you just want to ignore me, that's fine."
"Okay."
He walks away.
Back to his room.
His room looks normal.
Nash collapses on his bed and screams into his pillow. "AAAAAAAUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUU*UUUUUU**UUUUUUUUUGHHHHHHH!!!!!!"***

He continues to make intense vocalizations of severe emotional and physical distress before eventually falling asleep, curled in on himself, face bruised and yellowing like a rotten apple. It takes only minutes before he is gone, his body and heart somewhere else.

Aliza slowly rejoins them.

Donald takes a heavy death.

Aeolian and Theo remain conscious but with minimal health.
“Æ.” I mutter, still lying down.
Aliza tries to help him get up as the corpse slowly starts to shrink.
I get up, if possible.

It is. 

The monster shrinks into a single playing card, which Donald calmly collects and stores in his deck. "Jeez… Did we really have to do all that, Frank?"
“…Frank?”

"He means me." Frank Linjamin approaches from the back of the building with a knife to Maxwell’s throat.

"H-Help me! The empire will never stand for this!" Maxwell squirms.

"Mr Skylar!?" Aliza.
“Ghrk!” I tense up.

"We don't plan to hurt the old man. We just need Aliza Hamill to come with us. And we can't exactly risk her saying no. The queen wants to meet her." Donald.

"Ha... Long time no see, Lord Burr. Did you miss me?" Frank.

“Queen…?”
I address Frank. “Not particularly, nor has it been that long.”
"You've really never heard of the queen of the night? Well, whatever. We both know you can't handle stopping us in your condition. Just don't risk this old man's life and come with us." Donald.
“Whatever that means.” I shake my head.
"What?" Donald.
“Unclear.” I shake my head. “I don’t intend to get in your way right now.”

"Are you like... Stupid? This isn't a hard concept to grasp. It's a kidnapping. Whatever." Donald grabs Aliza by the arm and starts to drag her. She resists momentarily, but quickly decides to follow him out.
I follow after him.

The second Aeolian tries to do this, a knife is implanted in his back, dragging him below 0 hp. 

((End session. Remember to level up btw))
